----------------------------------------------------<br>
While this isn't the most preposterous claim I've read on this board, it comes close. I suppose you do not need a resurrection, EVER, as well? You've obviously not fought anything that can summon... well, at least hard enough to carry your weight. Keep your claims in the realm of plausibility and the rest of your commentary will be taken more seriously.<br>
-----------------------------------------------------<br>
<br>
No, I have not ever fought anything that can summon, so I am speaking based on my level of experience.  Perhaps &quot;ever&quot; was to strong of a word.  I should have said &quot;as long as things are going as planned.&quot;  I will sometimes need to be healed, just as sometimes a full group will be wiped out.  My point was that I don't have to plan on having a healer.<br>
<br>
Quote:<br>
-------------------------------------------------------<br>
At the end of the battle, the same amount of healing needs to be done. Adding a wizard to the party does not result in a party with a lower healing load.<br>
-------------------------------------------------------<br>
<br>
I never said it did.  You are assuming too much from my statement.<br>
<br>
You seem to think that I am disagreeing that casters need balance.  I am not.  I am saying that our balance can not be based solely on a dmg/sec comparison with a warrior (or monk, or any melee).<br>
<br>
Would it be fair for warriors if they put out equal sustained damage as a wizard yet they were not able to..<br>
-increase their damage rate as they see fit<br>
-gate back to their bind spot after dyeing<br>
-solo<br>
-evac the group<br>
<br>
I realize that the main focus of balancing is based on what each class brings to a group situation.  But these other abilities do matter.<br>
<br>
Like I said, I do think wizards, and all casters, need balancing.  I agree that a big part of that involves increasing our dmg/sec.  I just find it hard to believe that you cannot see any of the advantages of being a wizard. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/uoxoxoxoxox.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Oxoxo Xoxox</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/globalRainbow.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Evoker</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(4/10/02 11:04:18 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub23.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm10.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=710.topic&index=57>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://www2.swmed.edu/libraryis/eq/wizsig4.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Why do casters need balancing?</span><hr size=1> Its too complicated for you Dryfft, lets try again.<br>
