<br>
Monks and rogues aren't considered tanks yet they do the most damage.  Monks can actually tank OK if need be.<br>
<br>
Wizards, magician and necros primarily fill the same role as monks and rogues.  Of the three, wizards do by far the least damage outside of level 60 on certain raids.  Anybody who brings &quot;utility&quot; spells into the arguement can show me how much mana a grouped wizard spends on utility spells vs. damage spells.  The ratio is not even close.<br>
<br>
As for soloing, monks who are currently giving rogues a run for their money in high level damage, are able to bind wound up to 70% at 51.  Plus add 3 points per tick to hp regen with Natural Regeneration.  Don't forget Mend.  I don't know if First Aid stacks with their natural bandaging bonus but if it does they could bind up to 100%.<br>
<br>
I think what's happened to alot of longtime players of Everquest is like the old story about how to cook frogs.  <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START ;) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/wink.gif ALT=";)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->   You know, you don't put them in when the water's boiling hot or they'll freak and jump out of the pot.  Put them in when the water's still cool and by the time they notice they're getting cooked it's too late to jump out.<br>
<br>
At some point between EQ 1.0 and Kunark, Verant quietly decided that since casters have so much utility(LOL compare a bard's abilities to a wizard's utility sometime) that meleers should do more damage.  By -gradually- phasing out damage casters as damage dealers, Verant was able to lessen the outrage than if they had made the change overnight. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#33333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/uparacelsus01.showPublicProfile?language=EN>paracelsus01</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Wizard</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(4/11/02 2:15:09 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub23.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm10.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=710.topic&index=61>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: ....</span><hr size=1> @Oxoxo Xoxox: pssst, sometimes I get hit by AEs on raids too, and sometimes I have to stand in melee range to hit with my spells too.<br>
