<br>
So, you hit level 60, you get sunstrike.  Forget about Elnerick's, the spell is too rare to worry about right now.  Ice spear because of recast delay has a poor damage/second unless you alternate between spells.  You look at melees with their primal weapons and see their damage output.  You curse the lack of the promised focus items that are supposed to provide class balance through caster EQUIPMENT.<br>
<br>
Those with Luclin begin to push for AA skills, since between Spell Casting Mastery, Spell Casting Fury, and Spell Casting Fury Mastery, we get a boost that improves things, until we see the melees in their primal with THEIR AA skills.<br>
<br>
At the low end game, we see twinked melees left and right.  Twinked casters, even with focus items won't be able to compete without giving some DD items that are EASILY found.  Some mention Solist's icy wand, but we don't see a huge number of similar items to compensate for the TONS of twink melee weapons that are out there.  With all the melee items, we should see right-click DD items for casters in most zones that can be twinked if that's the way to offset melee twinking.<br>
